column5: Could someone enlighten me with a tackle shop that sells Trout roe bags instead of salmon in/near the Toronto area?  Thanks!

Many places are either out, or are down to crappy, white, half broken eggs, or else I wouldn't have harvested one.  Although this might be different now.  I'd suggest checking Tightline if you haven't yet.
Try "Al Flaherty's" on Dufferin (South of Eglinton)... Here's their website....  http://www.alflahertys.com/contact.php

Angling Specialties has trout roe, I picked up some yesterday.  They are on Central Parkway between Mavis and Hurontario.  Kind of hard to find but they are in the strip mall all Confederation.  Yellow sign.

If you live near by Oakvill and Milton, visit Brontoutdoor shop.  You may find out salmon, trout roe...  here is google map and site.   http://maps.google.com/maps/ms?ie=UTF8&amp...65a571&z=19  http://www.bronteoutdoor.com/
Rerries bait on Kingston rd. at Morningside Ave. Scarb.
Pro J Tackle on Sheppard Ave. E. (just east of Warden) has them in stock (unless they sold loads during last night & this morning...).
Thanks guys for all the replies!
PRO LINE at blackcreek and jane has them.
